## 5. Screens

### 5.1 Today Screen (Lane A)

**Purpose**: Daily planning & administrative triage.

**Blocks**:
- Today’s date & high-level summary.
- Calendar overview (today).
- Tasks needing attention.
- Emails needing response/decision.
- Suggested priorities.
- Proposed time blocks.
- “Questions for you” card.
- Preference-learning prompts (when applicable).

**Interactions**:
- Approve / edit / reject proposed time blocks.
- Mark tasks:
  - Must do today
  - Can wait
  - Defer
- Quick select duration: chips (15/30/45/60/90m/custom).
- Toggle urgency.
- Reorder priorities via drag-and-drop/reorder handles.
- Tap to mark email as:
  - Needs response
  - FYI only
  - Ignore/archive
- Confirm or refine inferred scheduling/priority preferences.
- Trigger re-run planning after changes.

**Mobile UI patterns**:
- Single-column stacked cards.
- Swipe actions (optional) for deferring/archive.
- Sticky bottom bar for “Approve plan” / “Update plan”.
- Bottom sheets for editing blocks.

