## 8. Model Routing & Cost Control

### 8.1 Model Roles

- **Gemini / Cheap Model**:
  - classification,
  - extraction,
  - clustering,
  - deduplication,
  - short bullet summaries,
  - email/task/topic tagging,
  - preference candidate drafting,
  - compact transform tasks.

- **Claude**:
  - executive brief synthesis,
  - resolving ambiguity (with preference retrieval),
  - preference distillation and misalignment analysis,
  - topic framing and thesis formation,
  - outline generation,
  - speaking notes,
  - complex trade-off explanation.

- **OpenAI (optional)**:
  - specialized tasks only if clearly justified,
  - or fallback / evaluation.

### 8.2 Routing Rules

- Use deterministic logic before models.
- Use cheap model by default; escalate only when:
  - complex weighing of trade-offs,
  - ambiguity/resolution involving preferences,
  - synthesizing long research reports,
  - generating outlines/notes.
- Parameterize maximum tokens per call.
- Track calls and tokens by model and workflow.

### 8.3 Cost-Reduction Techniques

- Use **structured UI** instead of chat back-and-forth.
- Persist state in DB instead of re-sending in prompt.
- Keep prompts narrow and step-specific.
- Use retrieval (preference & context) to add only relevant snippets.
- Batch operations (e.g., classify multiple emails in one call).
- Cache stable artifacts (Charter summary, preference snapshots, topic summaries).
- Implement daily or per-workflow cost caps.

