## 15. MVP Success Criteria

The MVP is successful if:

- You can log in via Google, and only you (or your allowlist) can access the app.
- On mobile, you can:
  - review the day,
  - accept/adjust a proposed plan,
  - handle key tasks & emails,
  - choose and steer topics,
  - confirm/refine preferences.
- The system:
  - uses Perplexity only for research when needed,
  - routes cheap vs expensive models sensibly,
  - keeps prompts short and state in the DB,
  - keeps operational state and actions auditable.

Everything else (chat UI, multi-user, additional lanes) is optional and can be layered on later.
